|GKB-- New Druid Flow ---------------------------------------------|000

The modern druid guild is built around two related ideas:

  Invocations are your fast active powers.
  Rituals prepare and shape the nwyfre that fuels them.

Your first useful path is:

|CKB1. Check nwyfre.|000

     |CKBnwyfre|000

   This shows your four vessels: Tellurian, Daloan, Marken, and
   Tekali.  The bars show how much power you have.  Regen and cost
   change with terrain, moon phase, current planet, groves, and
   active rituals.

|CKB2. Check your druid status.|000

     |CKBdscore|000
     |CKBgscore Druid|000

   These show your guild level and combat-earned Druid XP alongside
   study points, learned invocations, grove status, and profession
   materials.  Druid XP advances your guild level automatically when
   your regular level permits it.  Any blocked XP remains banked.
   The |CKBcost|000 and |CKBadvance guild|000 commands in the advancement
   cavern explain your next rank, but do not spend ordinary experience.

|CKB3. Learn a first invocation.|000

     |CKBlearn spirit aura|000

   Study invocations in the Druids' Meditation Grove inside the
   guild hall.  Use |CKBdhelp spells|000 to see every active invocation.

|CKB4. Gather profession materials.|000

     |CKBgather herbs|000
     |CKBmine ore|000
     |CKBskin corpse|000
     |CKBreagents|000

   Druid rituals and companions use the profession material stores:
   herbs, creature reagents, skins and leathers, ores and bars, bolts,
   and special shards.  Use |CKBreagents search <item>|000 to check
   exact balances.  Your silver sickle serves as a gardening spade,
   mining pick, and skinning knife, so you do not need to buy those
   three profession tools.  At Druid level 7, Verdant Refrain can also
   help by casually storing herbs and saved reagents as you travel
   through natural places.

|CKB5. Plant your Sacred Grove.|000

     |CKBgrove plant|000

   Plant it in a wild place you want to return to.  Later,
   |CKBcommune|000 returns you to your grove.  |CKBdhelp grove|000
   explains grove growth, return, and the inner sanctum.

|CKB6. Learn and perform a first ritual.|000

     |CKBlearn ritual drawing of the tide|000
     |CKBritual drawing of the tide marken|000

   Drawing of the Tide consumes profession materials matching the
   current you name and restores that current.  Use
   |CKBnwyfre ritual <name>|000 before learning or performing a ritual
   to see its requirements.

   Long-running rituals use the same ritual command, but toggle on and
   off.  For example:

     |CKBlearn ritual verdant refrain|000
     |CKBritual verdant refrain|000
     |CKBritual stop verdant refrain|000

|CKB7. Cast your first invocation.|000

     |CKBspirit aura|000

   Invocations spend nwyfre instead of spell points.  If an
   invocation says you lack nwyfre, use |CKBnwyfre|000 to see which current
   is low, then use rituals, time, terrain, or a grove to recover it.

|GKB-- Useful Commands --------------------------------------------|000

  |CKBnwyfre                |000 Show currents, active rites, and next steps.
  |CKBnwyfre learnable      |000 Show rituals you have not learned yet.
  |CKBnwyfre ritual <name>  |000 Inspect a ritual.
  |CKBdscore                |000 Show study, grove, and material guidance.
  |CKBdhelp spells          |000 List active invocations.
  |CKBdhelp ritual          |000 Learn the ritual system.
  |CKBdhelp grove           |000 Learn Sacred Groves.
